This paper is primarily focused on the implementation of a concurrent tabling system, which is a key feature of Prolog programming languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the design of a lock-free data structure, which is a common topic in the field of concurrent data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of atomic instructions and cache memory, which are relevant to the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.OS (Operating Systems). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results, which could fall under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
